Three traders were charged Monday with selling fake Uni-Gold HIV test kits and exporting them to Guyana in South America.
Erick Ndungâ€™u Mwangi, Jones Oluoch and Robert Njoya denied three counts of the offence before Milimani Chief Magistrate Martha Mutuku.
Mr Mwangi was separately charged with exporting 400 packets of counterfeit kits to Guyana on December 30, 2019, through the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport in Nairobi.



